# Assignment 1 – Deploy WordPress Using Terraform

## Objective
Deploy a WordPress site on AWS using Terraform.
The infrastructure includes an EC2 instance, security groups, and user data to install and configure WordPress automatically.

## Architecture Overview
- AWS EC2 instance (Amazon Linux)
- Security Group allowing HTTP (80) and SSH (22)
- User data script installs Apache, PHP, MariaDB, and WordPress
- Public endpoint exposed via EC2 public IP

## Terraform Files
- main.tf – Provider, EC2 instance, security group, and user data
- variables.tf – Input variables
- outputs.tf – Public IP and WordPress URL

## How It Works
1. Terraform provisions an EC2 instance in the default VPC
2. A security group allows inbound web traffic
3. User data installs and configures WordPress automatically
4. The site becomes accessible via the public IP

## Deployment Steps
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply

---
Terraform was used to ensure infrastructure could be recreated consistently and automatically without manual AWS configuration